            <fr:title text="Banach-Alaoglu theorem">Banach-Alaoglu theorem</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Theorem</fr:taxon>
            <fr:source-path>/Users/longie/forest/trees/FA-001R.tree</fr:source-path>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>The Banach-Alaoglu theorem states that the closed unit ball in the <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001Q.xml" addr="FA-001Q" title="Dual space">dual space</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X^*]]></fr:tex> of a normed vector space <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> is compact in the weak* topology.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Formally, the set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[B_{X^*} = \{f \in  X^* : ||f|| \leq  1\}]]></fr:tex> is compact in the weak* topology on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X^*]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>The weak* topology on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X^*]]></fr:tex> is the topology generated by the seminorms <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[p_x(f) = |f(x)|]]></fr:tex> for each <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x \in  X]]></fr:tex>. In this topology, a sequence <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f_n]]></fr:tex> converges to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> if and only if <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f_n(x) \to  f(x)]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x \in  X]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>This theorem is a fundamental result in functional analysis with numerous applications, including:</fr:p>
            <fr:ul><fr:li>Proving the existence of solutions to various optimization problems</fr:li>
<fr:li>Establishing the existence of minimizers in the calculus of variations</fr:li>
<fr:li>Providing a framework for studying <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000Y.xml" addr="FA-000Y" title="Weak Convergence">weak convergence</fr:link> of sequences of functionals</fr:li></fr:ul>
            <fr:p>The theorem is particularly powerful because it works in non-separable spaces and guarantees that every bounded sequence in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X^*]]></fr:tex> has a weak* convergent subsequence.</fr:p>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
