            <fr:title text="Convergence in norm">Convergence in norm</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:source-path>/Users/longie/forest/trees/FA-000Z.tree</fr:source-path>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>In a normed vector space <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[(X, ||\cdot ||)]]></fr:tex>, a sequence <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\{x_n\}]]></fr:tex> is said to converge in norm to an element <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x \in  X]]></fr:tex> if:</fr:p>
            <fr:p>
              <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\lim _{n \to  \infty } ||x_n - x|| = 0]]></fr:tex>
            </fr:p>
            <fr:p>This is also called strong convergence to distinguish it from other types of convergence such as <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000Y.xml" addr="FA-000Y" title="Weak Convergence">weak convergence</fr:link> or <fr:link type="local" href="FA-0010.xml" addr="FA-0010" title="Pointwise Convergence">pointwise convergence</fr:link>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Convergence in norm has the following properties:</fr:p>
            <fr:ul><fr:li>The limit is unique</fr:li>
<fr:li>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x_n \to  x]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[y_n \to  y]]></fr:tex> in norm, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[ax_n + by_n \to  ax + by]]></fr:tex> in norm for any scalars <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[b]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>If <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x_n \to  x]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[y_n \to  y]]></fr:tex> in norm, then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[||x_n|| \to  ||x||]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[||x_n - y_n|| \to  ||x - y||]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>In a complete normed space (<fr:link type="local" href="FA-000F.xml" addr="FA-000F" title="Banach Space">Banach space</fr:link>), every <fr:link type="local" href="FA-000X.xml" addr="FA-000X" title="Cauchy sequence">Cauchy sequence</fr:link> converges in norm to some element of the space</fr:li></fr:ul>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
        </fr:tree>
