            <fr:title text="Linear Functional">Linear Functional</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
            <fr:source-path>/Users/longie/forest/trees/FA-001P.tree</fr:source-path>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2025</fr:year>
              <fr:month>5</fr:month>
              <fr:day>26</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>Long Nguyen</fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter>
            <fr:p>A linear functional on a vector space <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[V]]></fr:tex> over a field <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> is a linear map <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f: V \rightarrow  F]]></fr:tex> from the vector space to its underlying field.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>In other words, a linear functional is a function <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f]]></fr:tex> that satisfies:</fr:p>
            <fr:ul><fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f(x + y) = f(x) + f(y)]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x, y \in  V]]></fr:tex> (additivity)</fr:li>
<fr:li><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f(\alpha  x) = \alpha  f(x)]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x \in  V]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[Î± \in  F]]></fr:tex> (homogeneity)</fr:li></fr:ul>
            <fr:p>In the context of functional analysis, linear functionals are particularly important when they are also continuous (or bounded) on normed spaces. The collection of all bounded linear functionals on a normed space <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> forms the <fr:link type="local" href="FA-001Q.xml" addr="FA-001Q" title="Dual space">dual space</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X^*]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>Examples of linear functionals include:</fr:p>
            <fr:ul><fr:li>Integration functionals: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f(g) = \int _a^b g(x) dx]]></fr:tex> on appropriate function spaces</fr:li>
<fr:li>Evaluation functionals: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f(g) = g(x_0)]]></fr:tex> for some fixed point <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[x_0]]></fr:tex></fr:li>
<fr:li>Inner products: For a fixed vector <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[v]]></fr:tex> in a Hilbert space, <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[f(x) = \langle  x, v \rangle ]]></fr:tex> defines a bounded linear functional</fr:li></fr:ul>
          </fr:mainmatter>
          <fr:backmatter />
